---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const lastUpdated = "July 14, 2026";
---

<Layout
  title="Disclaimer — PSUCheck"
  description="PSUCheck disclaimer: affiliate relationships, accuracy limitations, liability disclaimers, and non-endorsement policy for psucheck.com."
  noIndex={false}
>
  <div class="legal-page">
    <div class="legal-hero">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="badge badge-safe" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">Legal</div>
        <h1>Disclaimer</h1>
        <p class="legal-meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-body">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="legal-content">

          <h2>1. Affiliate Disclosure</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck participates in affiliate programs including <strong>Amazon Associates</strong>
            and the <strong>Newegg Affiliate Program</strong>. When you click a product link on this
            website and make a purchase, PSUCheck may earn a small commission at no additional cost to you.
          </p>
          <p>
            Affiliate relationships do not influence our calculator results, product recommendations, or
            editorial content. We recommend products based on technical specifications and value — not
            commission rates. PSUCheck is not a retailer and does not sell products directly.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Accuracy Disclaimer</h2>
          <p>
            All information on PSUCheck, including power supply recommendations, pricing estimates,
            component specifications, and cost projections, is provided for <strong>informational and
            educational purposes only</strong>. While we strive for accuracy, we make no guarantees that:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Wattage recommendations are accurate for every specific hardware configuration</li>
            <li>Pricing information reflects current market prices or availability</li>
            <li>Component specifications are free from errors or omissions</li>
            <li>Transient spike estimates match every individual unit's behavior</li>
          </ul>
          <p>
            Power supply requirements vary based on overclocking settings, ambient temperature, PSU age
            and quality, and specific component manufacturing variances. Our recommendations are
            starting points — verify requirements with your specific hardware documentation before purchasing.
          </p>

          <h2>3. No Professional Advice</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck's tools and content do not constitute professional engineering, electrical,
            or safety advice. PC building involves working with electrical components that can cause
            injury or property damage if handled improperly. If you are unsure about any aspect of
            your build, consult a qualified professional.
          </p>

          <h2>4. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law, PSUCheck and its operators shall not
            be liable for any damages arising from use of this website, including but not limited to:
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Hardware damage resulting from an undersized or incompatible power supply</li>
            <li>Financial losses from purchasing components based on our cost estimates</li>
            <li>Data loss or system instability resulting from power-related events</li>
            <li>Reliance on our calculator results for critical or commercial systems</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>5. External Links</h2>
          <p>
            PSUCheck contains links to third-party websites including retailer product pages,
            manufacturer specifications, and industry resources. We are not responsible for the
            content, accuracy, or practices of these external sites.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Changes to This Disclaimer</h2>
          <p>
            We may update this Disclaimer from time to time. The "Last updated" date at the top of
            this page reflects the most recent revision.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            For questions about this disclaimer, please use our <a href="/contact">Contact page</a>.
          </p>

        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
.legal-page {}
.legal-hero {
  padding: 4rem 0 2rem;
  background: linear-gradient(180deg, var(--bg-deep) 0%, var(--bg-primary) 100%);
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
}
.legal-meta {
  color: var(--text-tertiary);
  font-size: 0.875rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
}
.legal-body {
  padding: 3rem 0 5rem;
}
.legal-content {
  max-width: 760px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 1.5rem;
}
.legal-content h2 {
  font-size: 1.375rem;
  margin-top: 0.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border-subtle);
}
.legal-content p {
  color: var(--text-secondary);
  line-height: 1.75;
  max-width: 70ch;
}
.legal-content ul {
  padding-left: 1.5rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.4rem;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}
.legal-summary {
  font-size: 0.9375rem;
  line-height: 1.6;
  color: var(--text-secondary);
}
</style>
